`Issues` is an immutable (read-only) representation of the database
in git. It is made by creating a worktree containing a detached-head
checkout of the git ref, deserializing it, then removing the worktree
from the filesystem.

`IssuesMut` is a mutable (read/write) representation of the database in
git. It is made by creating a relatively long-lived worktree containing
a normal (named branch) checkout of the git ref, deserializing it,
and *leaving* the worktree on disk. The worktree is dropped when the
IssuesMut is dropped, and removed from the filesystem at that point.

Because the IssuesMut worktree is kept around, and because it contains
a named-branch checkout (not a detached head), it can be modified,
and the modifications can be added to the git ref by commit.

The new GitDb representation similarly presents GitDb (immutable) and
GitDbMut (mutable).
